wiki.summary: "I Hate U" is a song by American singer SZA. Originally released in August 2021 on her SoundCloud, along with two other songs ("Joni" and "Nightbird"), it eventually received a release on major platforms on December 3, 2021, after garnering popularity on the video-sharing app TikTok. A break-up song, it finds SZA detailing what went wrong in a past relationship, expressing resentment towards her ex, but acknowledging that she still misses them. wiki.content: "I Hate U" is a song by American singer SZA. Originally released in August 2021 on her SoundCloud, along with two other songs ("Joni" and "Nightbird"), it eventually received a release on major platforms on December 3, 2021, after garnering popularity on the video-sharing app TikTok. A break-up song, it finds SZA detailing what went wrong in a past relationship, expressing resentment towards her ex, but acknowledging that she still misses them. "I Hate U" is an electro-R&B song with a "crunching", dark instrumental, containing a relaxed, "ethereal" chorus, and hip hop-influenced verses. Read more on Last.fm.
